translation:
I desire not victory, O Krishna, nor kingdom, nor pleasures.
What use is dominion to us, O Krishna, or pleasures or even life?
commentary: 1.32 Not not? desire (I) desire? Vijayam victory? Krishna O Krishna? Not not? f and? kingdom kingdom? Sukhani pleasures? f and? What what? Nah to us? by the kingdom by kindom? Govinda O Govinda? What what? Bhogaih by pleasures? Life by life? or or.No Commentary.
